OL,6,F"I knew that it was a life-changing
OL,7,Frole for me, as an actor and just from
OL,8,Fa humanistic standpoint," Amos told
OL,9,FTime magazine.
OL,11,F"It was the culmination of all of the
OL,12,Fmisconceptions and stereotypical roles
OL,13,Fthat I had lived and seen being
OL,14,Foffered to me. It was like a reward
OL,15,Ffor having suffered those
OL,16,Findignities," he added.
